---

## 4️⃣ Opioid Crisis Monitoring
Dedicated opioid-focused dashboard analyzing:
- Opioid poisonings
- Severe ED cases
- Hospital admissions
- Mortality trends
- High-risk periods during COVID-19

### Intended Audience
- Harm Reduction Teams  
- Emergency Care Stakeholders  
- Addiction & Mental Health Services  

---

# 📊 Key Insights  
- Substance-related hospitalizations increased during the pandemic despite overall reductions in healthcare utilization.  
- Opioid poisonings showed significant increases during later pandemic months.  
- Lower-income populations experienced disproportionately higher hospitalization growth.  
- Severe substance-related healthcare cases increased during COVID-19.  
- Substance-related deaths increased in both ED and inpatient settings.  

